\begin{problem}{3.1.5 (10)} 
Let x and y be any two positive numbers. Using the definitions in Problems 3.1.3.and 3.1.4, show that $gcd(x, y) = \frac{xy}{lcm(x,y)}$

(a) by using the characterizations of gcd and lcm in terms of the prime factorization, and

(b) directly by proving that for any natural z, z is a common factor of x and y if and only if z divides xy and xy/z is a common multiple of x and y.

\end{problem}
