\begin{problem}{4.3.3 (5)}
Let the finite sequence a0,a1,...,an be defined by the rule ai = a0 · ri, where r is some
number not equal to 1. Prove by induction that the sum of the terms in the sequence is
$\frac{a_0-a_{n+1}}{1-r}$ (where $a_{n+1}$ is defined by the same rule even though it is not part of the sequence).
\end{problem}
